    # [Scene: Boardwalk | Evening — A Community Meal After a Day of Planting]
    hide maya_reyes
    hide professor_rowan_hale
    hide elias_stone

    scene bg ch13_601bcb_4 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Warm acoustic guitar picking underlaid by steady percussion; the melody feels like home]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Laughter, the slap of hands on hot paper plates, clinking thermoses]
    "You sit on the edge of the boardwalk with Elias and Lito, a paper plate between your knees. The marsh behind you breathes quietly like a creature beginning to heal. The industrial strip glows with cranes"
    "and floodlights in the distance, a reminder of what was conceded — but tonight the conversation hangs on apprenticeship schedules and the next round of monitoring."
    show amaya_chen at left:
        zoom 0.7

    amaya_chen "To the stewards. To the people who showed up when the machines did."
    "Crowd [cheers]"
    "Maya Reyes raises your thermos. The movement is small, but in it is the communal gravity of the last months: petitions drafted, training programs created, oversight boards formed, and a diminished but preserved neighborhood."
    show lito_reyes at right:
        zoom 0.7

    lito_reyes "You've grown teeth at the table, May. They listen now."
    show maya_reyes at center:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_reyes "We made them listen."
    "Camille Duval [across the way, holding a plate, tasting something new]: She catches your gaze and nods — a quiet, impartial salute rather than friendship. The tower behind her refracts the boardwalk lights; its presence is now tempered by oversight, by a stake in public scrutiny."
    "The victory is pragmatic: you kept most of what mattered and traded a thin strip for broader survival. It is not absolute. It will take decades of tending to make this shore what you imagine. But"
    "you and Elias Stone, and the people here, have a framework to do it — rights to steward land, jobs for locals, a voice in the decisions that shape the shoreline."
    hide amaya_chen
    show elias_stone at left:
        zoom 0.7

    elias_stone "Bruised, but resolved."

    maya_reyes "Bruised and still planting."
    "You think of the times you isolated, the nights of gnawed worry. Those moments remain; they are threads woven into a larger tapestry that now holds more people. Your guilt hasn't vanished — it has shifted"
    "into action, into teaching a teenager to plant Spartina and marking their first measuring point with them. That is a victory that grows."
    hide lito_reyes
    show professor_rowan_hale at right:
        zoom 0.7

    professor_rowan_hale "Measure triumph as persistence, Maya. The sea will test us; our job is to be better and keep trying."

    maya_reyes "Persistence,"
    "The final image settles: the marsh rising in slow, stubborn increments; children learning tide rhythms; a new generation of stewards with salted hands; a city that now holds a map where community voices have lines on"
    "it. You are tired, and you are elated. You are not healed fully — none of you are — but you are together, accountable, and alive to the work ahead."
    "You reach for Elias Stone's hand across the crate. He takes it, fit and warm, soil still under his nails. For the first time in a long while, your guilt rests as a kind of responsibility you can act on rather than a weight that crushes."

    "You stand, plate empty, and call out to the neighbors" "Tomorrow, at the fringe. Bring boots."
    "A chorus of affirmative replies rises like a tide."
    hide maya_reyes
    hide elias_stone
    hide professor_rowan_hale

    scene bg ch13_601bcb_5 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Swells into a cathartic, bright resolution — brass and strings harmonizing, then slowly easing into a soft close]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The gull's cry becomes a soft, single note that fades into the night]
    "You have learned to measure triumph as persistence. The ending here is not a finality of conquest but a promise kept and a promise renewed. You will keep showing up, and so will they. That is enough — not everything, but the work that matters."

    scene bg ch13_601bcb_6 at full_bg
    "THE END"
